<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Drunken" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Drunken,</orth> 1) intoxicated: <cit><quote>a d. brain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 910" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 910</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>is but d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 910" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 910</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. luc 703" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 703</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 155</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.1.96" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 1, 96</bibl>.  <bibl n="shak. shr 1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. I, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.207.138" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.207.138" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 207</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.3.23" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 3, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 4, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.219" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 219</bibl>.<lb />2) done in a state of intoxication: <cit><quote>d. sleep,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 150</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>d. prophecies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 33</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a d. slaughter,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 122</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>d. spilth of wine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 169</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) given to drink: <cit><quote>my d. butler,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.277" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 277</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your d. cousin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 5.312" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 312</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>so d. an officer,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.280" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 280</bibl></cit>.
